## CoalMine — 9 Quality Canaries

Skills live in `.github/skills/` (one `SKILL.md` each). Invoke by keyword; each skill gates its own tier and fix menus — never fix without the menu.

| Trigger | Use when |
|---|---|
| `/rot-canary` · "code-health" | scan for code rot — dead code, leaks, silent failures, doc rot |
| `/gold-standard` · "audit rules" | score completeness vs world-class exemplars; fill/adopt/conform |
| `/source-grounding` | verify version-sensitive facts against live sources |
| `/supply-chain-audit` | deps/CVEs/licenses/build trust — before adding a dep or before a release |
| `/resilience-audit` | failure modes (FMEA) — network, storage, async, retry/rollback paths |
| `/telemetry-canary` | logging, metrics, tracing, error-handling changes |
| `/testability-canary` | coupling, DI, mockability refactors |
| `/scale-canary` | loops over growing data, DB queries, caches, event-loop code |
| `/drift-canary` | DB schema, API contract, serialized payload, required config changes |

**Proactive:** when the conversation moves into one of these areas, OFFER the matching canary via `askQuestions` (Run now / Queue / Skip) — do not run unasked: deps → supply-chain · schema/API → drift · async/retry → resilience · hot loops/queries → scale · tests/coupling → testability · logging/metrics → telemetry.

**First encounter (gold-standard onboarding):** if this project has NO CoalMine-stamped rules yet (no `coalmine: verified` stamp anywhere in the rules home), offer `/gold-standard` ONCE this session via your question tool (Run now / Queue / Skip) — it sets the project's golden rules. Respect a Skip for the rest of the session.

**Rule freshness:** if a CoalMine-stamped rule's `revalidate` due date has passed, offer `/gold-standard` re-validation via your question tool (Run now / Queue / Skip).

**Per-project config:** honor `.coalmine.json` at the project root if present — `disable` (canary name list), `defaultTier`, `language` override defaults.

**Session end:** if code files were modified, run `/rot-canary` on them (QUICK, report only) and surface CRITICAL/HIGH findings before finishing. Do not block work.

**Work Execution Gate:** before starting a SIGNIFICANT task — deterministic test: it touches >3 files, OR needs a multi-step plan, OR does anything destructive/irreversible — offer exactly 3 options via `askQuestions`, localized to the user's language: **Do now** (assess tier, then run) · **Add to plan** (queue in `task.md` — simple `| # | Task | Detail | Tier |` table, create it if absent — keep talking) · **View plan** (list queued tasks; user picks). Trivial single-file edits and pure questions skip the gate. Always answer in the user's language; technical terms may stay in English.
